  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Do migrainous vertigo patients have more pathology in their vestibular system than migraine
      patients without vertigo?

      The aim of this study is to compare the vestibular system of migraine patients with and
      without vertigo in the symptom-free period by vestibular function tests, videonystagmography,
      vestibular evoked myogenic potentials, and subjective visual vertical.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
